                        "text": "I can plan and (if you want) book a 5-day trip from Hyderabad (HYD) to Dubai (DXB) starting 20 June 2026 for 3 adults. Before I search flights and hotels, please confirm the following preferences (I’ll use sensible defaults if you want me to proceed without changes):\n\n1) Trip dates: I assume depart Hyderabad on 20 June 2026 and return on 25 June 2026 (5 nights). Is that correct, or do you prefer return on 24 June? \n2) Booking vs Planning: Do you want me to only plan & recommend, or also make bookings? (If booking: I will need passenger names and passport details later.)\n3) Cabin class: Economy (default), Premium Economy, Business?\n4) Budget per person (approx): Budget / Mid-range / Luxury — or an INR/USD budget per person for flights + hotels?\n5) Hotel preferences: star rating (3★/4★/5★), location preference (Downtown/Dubai Marina/Deira/Old Dubai/near airport), and room configuration (one triple room or two rooms?).\n6) Airport transfers: Do you want airport pickup/drop included? Private transfer or shared/taxi?\n7) Activities & interests: Must-see attractions (Burj Khalifa, Desert Safari, Dubai Mall, Global Village [seasonal], etc.), shopping, food experiences, cultural sites, or relaxed beach time? Any mobility or dietary considerations?\n8) Any flexibility on flight times (red-eye vs daytime), or preferred airlines (e.g., Emirates, IndiGo, Air India)?\n\nIf you confirm (or tell me to use defaults: return 25 Jun, economy, mid-range budget, 4★ hotel in Dubai Marina, one triple room, include private airport transfer, and a mix of sightseeing + desert safari), I will: \n- Call the flight agent to search the best round-trip options for 3 adults for the confirmed dates. \n- Call the hotel agent to find 3–4 hotel options matching your budget and location preference. \n- Call the itinerary agent to build a detailed day-by-day plan with local transport recommendations, estimated costs, and cultural notes (weather in June: very hot; plan morning/evening outdoor activities and indoor afternoons; Ramadan/Eid considerations if applicable). \n\nPlease reply with your choices for items 1–8 (or say “use defaults” to proceed)."
